    "discriminators": [
     "The steady wind bed and the baseline of the category: long, stationary, LF-weighted broadband noise in a wide stereo image. It is defined by what it is NOT — the low-flux, low-centroid-deviation floor its siblings depart from.",
     "Steadier than WIND-GUST, which is one rise-fall swell: GUST triples spectral_flux and spectral_centroid_deviation_hz and halves stationarity and sustain_ratio.",
     "Quieter and calmer than WIND-TURBULENT (roughly half the root_mean_square_level, less LF weight).",
     "Noise, not tone: harmonicity is gated below 0.60, which is exactly where WIND-TONAL begins.",
     "Broadband, not micro-eventful: WIND-VEGETATION inverts the spectral tilt (high_band_energy dominant) because you are hearing leaves, not air."
    ],
