    "discriminators": [
     "Wind heard THROUGH a building. The structure is a low-pass filter and an attenuator, so the signature is LP + QUIET + NARROW: band_limit_high_hz falls to a few kHz, low_band_energy rises to ~0.50, root_mean_square_level drops to ~0.05, and the image collapses (stereo_width ~0.30). That triple is the real handle.",
     "Against WIND-GENERAL (exterior): exterior wind keeps its HF and its wide image. Interior wind cannot.",
     "The UCS text defers the tonal cases explicitly — 'see also WIND-TONAL for overtly tonal winds and whistles' — so if harmonicity climbs past ~0.5 (a moan through a chimney or a whistle at a window crack), prefer WIND-TONAL even though the bed is LP-filtered."
